Title: Few observations related to lastname field validations

1. Tried giving numbers in lastname field.
Request Body:
{
    "roomid": 70,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": 1234,
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    },
    "email": "abc.def@example.com",
    "phone": "12345678900"
}
Expected Behavior:
400 error with meaningful message

Actual Behavior:
201 Created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 4,
    "roomid": 70,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "1234",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

2. Tried giving decimal in lastname field.
Request Body;
{
  "roomid": 71,
  "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": 12.33,
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}
Expected Behavior:
400 error with meaningful message

Actual Behavior:
201 created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 5,
    "roomid": 71,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "12.33",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

3. Tried giving boolean in lastname field.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 72,
  "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": true,
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

Expected Behavior:
400 error with meaningful message

Actual Behavior:
201 created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 6,
    "roomid": 72,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "true",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

4. Tried giving special characters in lastname field. It accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 73,
  "firstname": “ABC”,
  "lastname": "DEF@%",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 7,
    "roomid": 73,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "DEF@%",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

5. Tried giving leading and trailing spaces in lastname field. It accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 74,
  "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": " DEF ",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

6. Tried giving numbers mixed in lastname field. It accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 75,
  "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": "DEF123",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

7. Tried giving symbols only in lastname field. It accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 76,
  "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": "@#$%^",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}
